canonical:
  title: 臨水杏花
  author: 成俔
  language: lzh
  text: 瓠犀齒白捲唇紅蘭麝淸香散曉風似怕嬌顔容易老淡施脂粉照靑銅
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 臨水杏花
  author: 成俔
  language: lzh
  text: 瓠犀齒白捲唇紅。蘭麝淸香散曉風。似怕嬌顔容易老。淡施脂粉照靑銅。
korean:
  title: 임수 행화
  author: 성현
  language: kor
  text: |-
    박씨 같이 이는 흰데 걷어올린 입술은 붉었고나
    난사의 맑은 향기는 새벽 바람에 픙긴다
    아리따운 얼굴이 쉽게 늙을까 두려워 하는 것처럼
    연지와 분을 옅게 바르고 거울에 비쳐 본다
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1450_020_0800&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Apricot Blossoms by the Water
  author: Seong Hyeon
  language: eng
  text: |-
    White teeth like gourd seeds, lips curved and crimson—
    the clear fragrance of orchid and musk drifts on the dawn breeze.
    Fearing her fair face will fade too quickly with the years,
    she applies rouge and powder lightly, gazing at her reflection in the bronze mirror.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'gourd seeds' (瓠犀) is a classical Chinese metaphor for perfect white teeth, drawn from the Shijing.
  - key: ''
    value: The 'bronze mirror' (靑銅) references the traditional mirrors of East Asia, and here symbolizes both vanity and the passage of time.
